Teltoli gave a little yelp as she was shoved off the rock, and 
managed to catch herself before she tumbled to the ground.

"Another boulder? ANTOTHER ONE? Arrgghh!!" She threw her hands up in 
mock-surrender and made to pull her bottom lip down in a pout.. but 
decided against it. 

"You and your boulders.." The Fuzor muttered before taking off again 
to the sky.

She knew the track, and made it to the bog in a shorter time, much to 
her pleasure. When she was landing by it, she spotted some of the 
black moss Carnage had been talking about. It looked.. icky. 

Tentivly she prodded a finger at it, and found that it wasn't as 
disgusting as it looked. Grabbing a few pints of it, the Fuzor stored 
it in a large leaf she had found on a bush nearby. Deciding she 
should take this back first before she found another boulder, Teltoli 
flew up into the sky and jetted back to the clearing.

Reaching her friend, she discovered that somehow she had flown pretty 
far up into the sky.. higher than what was usually needed. Teltoli 
smiled and enjoyed the view for a moment, before landing softly in 
the clearing.

"There! Moss! Yech!" She said in close-disgust and she put the leaf 
full of moss down by the boulder, and positioned herself on the 
boulder.

"I am -so- not moving until you tell me what you need the boulder 
for! And that Moss stuff!" The Fuzor said stubbornly, crossing her 
arms across her chest. A small hint of a smile kept tugging at her 
face, even though she was trying to remain serious.
